From 78b565e69341bab3b6a5a534b3f8ad35ec588441 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: YounghwanJoo <neokein@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 17 Mar 2026 23:58:09 +0900
Subject: [PATCH] Add DPU composition panel; visual polish; split UI buffers
 per DPU plane
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Visual improvements:
- Move rotation (R) badge from DPU node to preview_buf (the buffer DPU rotates)
- R badge positioned top-right; C/L badges top-left. All badges track node drag.
- Layer background color bands (app/fw/hal/kernel/hw/memory) behind canvas nodes
- Node drop shadow via Cytoscape shadow-* properties
- Buffer nodes: barrel shape + vertical gradient for cylinder appearance

DPU Composition panel (WinScope-style):
- New schema: Size, Rect, DpuPlane, DpuComposition models in models.py
- DpuComposition has display_id (links to pipeline node) + display_name
- ScenarioFile.dpu_compositions: list — supports foldable/multi-display (display0, display1)
- Clicking a display node shows miniature display preview + per-plane detail cards
- Each plane card shows buffer, source_crop, display_frame, transform

Buffer architecture fix:
- Replace single ui_buf (1080x2340, full-screen) with dedicated per-plane buffers:
  status_buf  (ARGB8888 1080x96)  — SystemUI: clock, battery → DPU plane 1
  controls_buf(ARGB8888 1080x324) — CameraApp: shutter, mode switcher → DPU plane 2
- Each DPU plane now maps 1:1 to a distinct pipeline buffer node
- Update edges: gpu→status_buf, gpu→controls_buf, status_buf→dpu, controls_buf→dpu

Code cleanup (simplify):
- LAYER_BANDS and DPU_COMP_MAP moved to module scope (avoid per-event re-allocation)
- DPU planes pre-sorted by z_order at init; showNodeDetail uses O(1) map lookup
- createBadgeEl() helper removes badge DOM creation duplication
- drawLaneDividers event registrations unified to cy.on('resize pan zoom', ...)
- transform field: Literal type for compile-time validation
- display_size uses Size(w,h) model; Rect(x,y,w,h) kept for source_crop/display_frame
